sentences: Craig Anthony Bullock, also known by his stage name DJ Homicide (born December 17, 1970), is an American musician, DJ, rapper, singer, record producer and radio personality.
On August 22, 2010, it was announced on Sugar Ray's Twitter page that Bullock had left the band.
The genre of his musical library is diverse, but primarily contemporary (1980s—present day).
On top of his work with Sugar Ray, Bullock spends a great deal of time as a solo artist, appearing as a featured DJ at nightclubs all across the country.
Most notably he can be heard in the hook of "Every Morning" saying "Shut the door baby, don't say a word."
With the band, Bullock has appeared in the films Scooby-Doo and Father's Day and the TV show Las Vegas.
